header.gameNote: SHAMROCK OFFICE SOLUTIONS CLASSIC AT MORAGA CA

article.headline: San Francisco St. 71, Jacksonville St. 68
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. -- Nefi Perdomo had 24 points and nine assists to lead San Francisco State to a 71-68 victory over Jacksonville State in the consolation game of the Shamrock Office Solutions Classic on Monday night. James Albright added 19 points and six rebounds for the Gators (2-5), a Division II squad. Griffin Reilly, a transfer from Loyola Marymount, had 11 points and 10 rebounds. Mason Leggett had 17 points and six rebounds for the Gamecocks (2-5), who played their third game in four nights. Stephen Hall added 11 points and five rebounds. Jacksonville State went on a 16-7 run to cut San Francisco State's lead to 65-63 with 45.2 seconds remaining. But Perdomo made a pair of free throws, and the Gamecocks' Brian Williams missed a 3-point attempt. The Gators made 3 of 5 free throws in the final seconds to hold on.
